Table (ref) shows results for the Web dataset, with different stage-1 configurations, and default {\em thr80} for scrutinization.
By and large, the results reconfirm our key findings with the Books data:
LLM-only methods are far inferior;
all L3X-RAG methods boost recall;
the {\em amp} has the best AUC after Stage 1 and is the overall winner for R@P after Stage 2.
The oracle-based upper bound here is 65% for recall from top-{{2405.02732_FO0071||FO}}=500 passages.